Constraints 
-------------
- Data integrity- Store only valid data in table.
- Data integrity is a process that ensures only valid data should be stored in the database table. 
- Constraints are used to prevent invalid data entry into our table. 
- If table having null values then we can't add contrants.

- 2 Level  constants-
  1)Column level 
  ---------------
  - Allow for all keys
  
  2)Table level( Composite unique key):
  - Allows all key but not allow not null.
  - Uniqueness by combining more than one column.(rg- name+mob=unique)
  - Table level constant = create composite unique key/ composite primary key.
  - Single primary key with multiple columns called composite key.
    CREATE TABLE employee( 
    eno int, 
    name varchar(20), 
    primary key(eno, name) 
    ); 


  
- We have following types of constraints: 

1)  Not null 
  ---------
  - Null value = not allowed.
  - Duplicate value = allowd
    Example
    -------
    Name= Not null but allow duplicate value.
    Example
    ------
    Column Level 
  ---------------------
  CREATE TABLE employee( 
  eno int not null, 
  name varchar(20) 
  ); 

   Insert Record 
  --------------
  INSERT INTO employee values(1,'Ram'); 
  INSERT INTO employee values(null,'Ram'); 
  Error:  Column 'eno' cannot be null 
  

  Table Level Syntax 
  ------------------
  CREATE TABLE employee( 
  eno int not null, 
  name varchar(20), 
  not null(eno,name) 
  ); 
  - Error:  not null not support table level


  2) Unique 
  -------
  - Null value =  allowed.
  - Duplicate value = not allowd
    Example
    -------
    email, mob

    Column level
    -------------
    CREATE TABLE employee( 
    eno int unique, 
    name varchar(20) 
    ); 

    SELECT * FROM employee; 
    INSERT INTO employee values(1,'Ram'); 
    INSERT INTO employee values(null,'Ram'); 
    INSERT INTO employee(name) values('Ram'); 
    INSERT INTO employee values(1,'Swam'); 

-If you want to add more then two column in unique used table level.
-Eg(eco+name)
- Technically this is called Composite unique key.

    Composite unique key
    -------------------
    Table level
    ------------
    CREATE TABLE employee( 
    eno int, 
    name varchar(20), 
    unique(eno, name) 

  
 3) Primary key 
  -----------
  - Null value = Not allowed.
  - Duplicate value = not allowd
  - One table maximum one primary key.
  

    Example
    -------
    aadhar card

    CREATE TABLE employee( 
    eno int primary key, 
    name varchar(20) 
    ); 
    DESC employee; 
    SELECT * FROM employee; 
    INSERT INTO employee values(1,'Ram'); 
    INSERT INTO employee values(null,'Ram'); 
    INSERT INTO employee(name) values('Ram'); 
    INSERT INTO employee values(1,'Swam'); 


  Apply constraint on Existing Table
  ----------------------------------
  - If table is empty / it name column not having null value;
  - Alter table emp CHANGE name name varchar(20) not null;
                          OR
  - Alter table emp ADD CONSTRAINT UNIQUE(mobno);
  
    For primary key
    ---------------
    Alter table emp ADD Primary Key(mobno);
     

  DELETE CONTRAINT
  ----------------
  For(any CONSTRAINT)
  - Alter table emp DROP CONSTRAINT mobno;
  For primary key
  - Alter table emp DROP Primary key;
  
  Check contraint
  ---------------
  age=18 to 60
  mobileno=10digit
  course=DE,DS
- This constraint is used to define logical conditions according to our business rule. 
  Example#1 
  ---------
  create table student( 
  age int check (age between 10 and 20) 
  ); 
  INSERT INTO student VALUES(5); 
  INSERT INTO student VALUES(15); 
  INSERT INTO student VALUES(25); ->error

  Example#2 [Table Level Constraint]
  ----------------------------------
  create table student( 
  mobno bigint,
  constraint check_mobileno check(length(mobno) = 10) 
  ); 
  INSERT INTO student VALUES(123456789); 
  INSERT INTO student VALUES(12345678910); 
  INSERT INTO student VALUES(1234567891); 

Example#3 
---------
  create table student( 
  course varchar(30) check(course in('Data Engineering','DevOps')) 
  ); 
  INSERT INTO student VALUES('Data Science'); 
  INSERT INTO student VALUES('devops'); 
  INSERT INTO student VALUES('Data Engineering'); 

